<p class="p">The assignment of scores allows the aggregation of the variables that comprise each index through the arithmetic mean, which is the second step. These indices can be observed in the column “calculation of the indices” shown in 
 <xref ref-type="table" rid="pone.0190808.t001" class="xref">Table 1</xref> and in the orange boxes of the methodological scheme (
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="pone.0190808.g003" class="xref">Fig 3</xref>). However, the final value of the arithmetic mean does not vary between 0 and 1, as defined to represent the indices, so values of arithmetic means are standardized such that they range from 0 to 1 (
